Hybrids of earth species are not xeno, this on the other hand is real xeno beauty.

title: Crew Objectives
body:
:cl: Citadel (of all places), ported by ike709
add: Crew objectives are now a thing. Now you can get greentext without being an antag. If, for some ridiculous reason, you don't want an objective, it can be disabled in your game preferences.
/:cl:

Before any jimmies are rustled, note that I plan on making this a player preference for if they want to have objectives or not. Also, I removed miscreant objectives because I'm not comfortable with adding Tator Lite until the greytide has been dealt with.

title: [READY]Very minor Ashwalker buffs
body:
:cl: 
balance: Ashwalkers are now ashstorm immune and have shadow eyes
/:cl:

[why]: # Life is very hard for ashwalkers, and most seem to end up dead before they can bring corpses back to feed the tendril. I feel like they need *something*, but I didn't want to go overboard with the buffs by any stretch of the imagination. I think this is a good starting point.

title: Adds translators / Removes Galactic Common from Ethari
body:
:cl: ike709
add: Translator badges are now a thing. While equipped, it grants a specific language. Currently, they only exist for Galactic Common. More coming soon.
tweak: Ethari no longer speak Galactic Common. Something something vocal chords and anatomy. Now they have a translator badge for it. Replacements can be found in ClothesMates and autolathes.
/:cl:

You have no fucking idea how long I stared at saycode trying to make this work until I remembered that krav maga gloves were a thing and just did it the same way they handle martial arts.

Surprisingly, this method worked first try.

Okay so I'm tired of Ethari being a reskin with damage modifiers... So I did this. Their very own gimmick. Translators are kind of a neat idea in general, though.

TODO:
- [x] Sprites.
- [x] Add checks to make sure it doesn't add/remove the language to/from a species that already has it.
- [x] Ways of getting them in game aside from spawning with them. ~~Cargo? R&D? Map them in? Add them to a vendor?~~ Autolathe and ClothesMate.
- [x] Make sure Ethari still get them if the neck slot is occupied.
- [x] ~~Maybe add translators for other languages and add ways to get them?~~ Follow-up PR.
- [x] ~~Translation collar that includes every language?~~ Follow-up PR.
- [x] Further testing.

I've decided to hold off on adding collars for other languages until a follow-up PR so this PR doesn't get delayed due to balance memes.

~~Currently just waiting on sprites.~~

title: Medical rework v0.2
body:
# I seriously can't spend so much time on coding because of my finals, so this will remain here until either someone takes it and makes it nice or I'm done with school.

Stuff that's there:
* Almost all organs can be damaged
* Almost all organs give significant drawbacks when damaged; potentially lethal
* A sorta-universal way to apply special effects on organs being damaged
* Sharp things damaging organs more; blunt things breaking bones more

Stuff that's almost there:
* The body scanner is *almost* ready, but someone needs to tweak the UI a bit and make sure it works as intended

Stuff that's NOT there:
* Actual thinking put into how damaged organs affect PCs and how badly they should fuck people up
* An actual, more complex medical system that will be a bigger challenge for medbay staff, à la Bay
* Non-linear surgery (I am so sorry)
